        "text": "king’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "seer, because the king took special delight in him; or because he frequently attended the king in his palace, executing his sacred office there, while the rest were employed in the tabernacle. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "In the words of God — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To sing such divine songs as were inspired by God to the prophets or holy men of God. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "To lift up the horn — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To praise God with the sound of a trumpet, or some other musical instrument made of horn, which, being a martial kind of music, might be most grateful to David’s martial spirit: though he was also skilled in other instruments of music which he used in the house of God.",
        "children": []
