  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "All these were the sons of Heman, the king's seer,.... The prophet of the king, as the Targum, who was frequently with him, assisting him ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in the words of God: in divine things: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to lift up the horn; to blow with the hornpipe or trumpet, and to magnify and set forth the greatness of the kingdom of Israel, and especially of the King Messiah, the horn of salvation, that would be raised up in the house of David: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and God gave to Heman fourteen sons; whose names are before mentioned: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and three daughters; of whom we have no more account, only may observe, that both are the gifts of God, and an heritage from him, Psalm 127:3. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and three daughters; of whom we have no more account, only may observe, that both are the gifts of God, and an heritage from him, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
